
** Archive Log

  - If the archive log is enabled then it's possible to restore a
    corrupted data file and recover the consistency of the database
    with the recovery tools by rolling 'it forward in time by applying
    archives to it'. So storing of the redo log files makes less
    sense. Best would be to place the files to different disks.

** Enable Logs

  - SQL> shutdown;
  - SQL> startup mount nine;
  - SQL> alter database archivelog;
  - SQL> alter database open;


** Disable Logs

  - SQL> alter database noarchivelog;

** Backup

  - SQL> alter tablespace midba begin backup;
  - SQL> alter tablespace midba end backup;


** Switch Logs

  - SQL> archive log list;
  - SQL> alter system switch logifle;
  - SQL> select * from v$log;
  - SQL> select * from v$logfile;

** init.ora parameters

  - = log_archive_start  = true (is mandatory)
  - = log_archive_dest   = has defaults
  - = log_archive_format = has defaults

** Archive Destination: Method1

  - = log_archive_dest        = /O1/oracle/oradata/arch
  - = log_archive_duplex_dest = /O2/oracle/oradata/arch

** Archive Destination: Method2

  - = log_archive_dest_1      = 'Location = /O1/oracle/oradata/arch' =
  - = log_archive_dest_2      = 'Service = standby ' =

